{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17493286","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17493286"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T07:04:00+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T07:04:00+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1276"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"1276","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/1276"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.04,0.74,0.02,0.18,0.01]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1276"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"39813"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"1276","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/1276"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1276"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"24321"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"4"},{"type":"tags","id":"6"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"141"},{"type":"tags","id":"4962"},{"type":"tags","id":"4974"},{"type":"tags","id":"4977"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"4992"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11626"},{"type":"tags","id":"11633"},{"type":"tags","id":"11642"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"2935"},{"type":"contributions","id":"2962"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42273"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43067"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"39813","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/39813"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 70-year-old woman from a nursing home undergoes a routine dual energy X-ray absorptiometry (DEXA) scan for bone mineral density. She has not had any recent falls. She does not complain of any pain. Her medical history includes oesophageal stricture, breast cancer (treated with lumpectomy and radiotherapy), atrial fibrillation, fractured left neck of femur, and glaucoma.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHer DEXA scan reveals a Z-score of -1.5 and T-score of -2.7. Her blood tests are as follows:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003ECalcium 2.30 mmol/L (Normal: 2.10 - 2.60 mmol/L)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003ECreatinine 90 \u00b5mol/L (Normal: 45- 90 \u00b5mol/L)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EPhosphate 1.0 mmol/L (Normal: 0.75- 1.50 mmol/L)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EParathyroid hormone 50 ng/L (Normal: 14-65 ng/L)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E25-Hydroxy vitamin D 80 nmol/L (Normal: \u2265 50 nmol/L)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EEstimated glomerular filtration rate 70 mL/min/1.73 m^2\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Low bone mass","Osteoporosis","Paget\u0027s disease","Osteopenia","Osteomalacia"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOsteoporosis\u003C/strong\u003E is defined as a low bone mineral density, with a T score of \u0026lt;-2.5. This woman has a T-score of -2.7, which means her bone mineral density is 3 standard deviations below the average for a young, healthy individual of the same gender. This is diagnostic for osteoporosis in the absence of other causes, such as severe vitamin D deficiency.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPaget\u0027s disease\u003C/strong\u003E is a disease that causes chronic enlargement and weakening of bones secondary to increased and uncontrolled bone turnover with\u00a0excessive osteoclastic resorption followed by increased osteoblastic activity. In this condition, bone mineral density generally increases, (resulting in an increased T-score), thus, it is unlikely that this patient has Paget\u0027s disease.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOsteopenia\u003C/strong\u003E is a diagnosis that is defined by a T-score between -1.0 and -2.5. This is otherwise known as \u003Cstrong\u003Elow bone mass\u003C/strong\u003E.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOsteomalacia\u003C/strong\u003E is defined as a decreased bone mineral content secondary to low vitamin D levels. This patient does has a normal vitamin D level and osteomalacia can be ruled out.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Osteoporosis can be diagnosed when bone mineral density T-score is \u003C-2.5 on DEXA bone scan. Do not confuse T-score and Z-score.","DEXA T-score: Comparison of a person\u0027s bone density with a healthy 30-year old person of the same SEX and ETHNICITY.","DEXA Z-score: Comparison of a person\u0027s bone density with an average person of the same AGE, SEX and ETHNICITY."],"references":["Akkawi I, Zmerly H. Osteoporosis: Current Concepts. Joints. 2018 Jun 14;6(2):122-127. doi: 10.1055/s-0038-1660790. PMID: 30051110; PMCID: PMC6059859.","Winzenberg T, Jones G. Dual energy X-ray absorptiometry. Australian Family Physician. 2011 (40):43-44."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"24321"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1276"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"24321","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/24321"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2023-10-08T20:48:57+10:30","updatedAt":"2023-10-08T20:48:57+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1276"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"39813"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"4","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4"},"attribute